<br>
Strikes me that quests should be like this:<br>
<br>
Quest involves TLC items and the item you get is similar in level to the easiest part of the quest<br>
<br>
This means that the highest level mob in a quest should be kill able by someone who can get the lowest level mob without getting a TLC.<br>
<br>
This is how quest should be and alas are not.<br>
<br>
Another solution for quests is that there should be more than 1 path for the quest. Take the monk quests, if you are not a lvl 60 grand master but you forgot to do your sashes then take the higher level sash tests.<br>
<br>
Still this would take work.<br>
<br>
Another simpler solution would be GM interaction. If you want to get X for your epic, you can petition and a GM will give you things to collect. When you have em you get the item.<br>
<br>
