<br>
How about any item associated with a quest is not affected by TLC? Might be a simpler solution.<br>
<br>
I also think they can prevent people from hoggin camps by using the new code they have implemented in SoL. This code increases either:<br>
<br>
a) The spawn rate of the mob, or<br>
b) the level of the mob.<br>
<br>
In the first case once, once a rare (or its place holder) spawns and is killed, 15 minutes could be added to the re-spawn time. If the creature is left alive for &quot;x&quot; amount of time then the respawn rate is reset.<br>
<br>
In the second case, the respawn time does not change, but the level of the mob increases. This makes it increasingly more difficult to keep the camp. I believe in this case, once the creature is left alive for &quot;x&quot; amount of time it despawns, and the &quot;original&quot; re-spawns.<br>
<br>
